The paper deals with online scheduling algorithms, which is a topic in computer science that falls under several sub-categories. The use of competitive analysis suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The focus on maximizing the total processing time of accepted jobs suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The use of algorithms to make decisions in real-time suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of a slack parameter and the need to make decisions based on deadlines suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the use of deterministic algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
